Principal Components Analysis on Nutrients

Benson Truong

Introduction

Nutrients provides nourishment essential for metabolism and the maintainance of life. Therefore, it is important to be cautious of the food we eat and be aware of food that have good nitritional value. In this study, common nutrients are analyzed for possible correlations between restuarants and fast foods. Data was taken from the United States Department of Agriculture FoodData Central.

Figure 3. Photo of many foods with good nutritional value. Credit: Corrie Cooks

Figure 4. A PCA biplot exploring nutrients correlation between restaurants and fast foods.

Summary:
  • Carbohydrates and fibers are highly postively correlated
  • Fats and carbohydrates have no correlation
  • Sugars and proteins are negatively correlated
  • All variables have similar variances
